{"by":"trevor-e","id":47772330,"parent":47768750,"text":"This looks pretty neat and the anti-AI hate in here is getting pretty tiresome.<p>From what I can tell looking at the codebase compared to Django&#x27;s, the top-level modules are structured much better and more obvious for AI to discover them. And then inside each module is a descriptive README with lots of description and examples that are helpful to an agent (and human). Not sure why this is being written off as slop or arbitrary changes, it seems pretty obvious to me this is the direction of frameworks.","time":1776205988,"type":"comment"}